parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the low beam HID headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, and may lead to fines or penalties for driving without proper lighting.
symptoms: The low beam headlights do not turn on
or are dim
or have a yellowish tint
or are foggy
or have a haze
or are not functioning properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of replacement parts for the low beam HID headlights can lead to extended periods of time without proper lighting, increasing the risk of accidents, and may lead to fines or penalties for driving without proper lighting.
symptoms: The dealer or manufacturer is unable to provide replacement parts
or the parts are on backorder
or the cost of replacement is excessive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blend door actuator/module can cause the windshield defroster to malfunction, resulting in reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially in cold weather conditions.
symptoms: The defroster blows cold air instead of heat
the windshield remains foggy or icy
the heater and air conditioning system malfunction
and the climate control system fails to operate properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure to Correct Action under Recall 05S28 (NHTSA Campaign Number: 07V336000)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to correct the issue under recall 05S28 can lead to unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and increased risk of accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: None reported
as the issue is related to the failure of dealerships to perform the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Parts for Recall 05S28 (NHTSA Campaign Number: 07V336000)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed or unavailable parts for recall 05S28 can lead to unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and increased risk of accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Dealerships stating that parts are not available or on backorder
failure to perform the recall repair
and repeated scheduling and rescheduling of appointments.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vehicle Speed Control Deactivation and Erratic Movement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deactivation of the vehicle speed control can lead to unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and increased risk of accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Erratic vehicle movement
smoke coming from the cabin and under the hood
electrical smell surrounding the vehicle
and deactivation of the speed control switch.
